    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="mt-20">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h3 class="fade-in-up text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">FAQ</h3>
        <p class="fade-in-up text-lg text-gray-600">Quick answers about trial access, multi-node usage, licensing, and support.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-4">
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">Can I request an invoice?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">Yes. Invoice applications are supported, and electronic invoices are sent by email after processing.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">Is there a free trial for 1Panel Pro?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">Yes. You can apply for a 30-day free trial by sending an email request to <a class="text-1panel hover:underline" href="mailto:hi@lxware.hk?subject=1Panel Pro: 30-Day Free Trial Request">hi@lxware.hk</a>.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">Can one license be used on multiple devices at the same time?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">No. One license can be bound to one device at a time, but it can be unbound and rebound to another device.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">How does multi-node capability work in Pro Edition?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">Node Management is a Pro feature: you get a unified console for multiple servers—node switching, monitoring, batch updates, and file transfer between nodes. See the <a class="text-1panel hover:underline" href="https://1panel.pro/docs/v2/user_manual/xpack/node/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Node Management</a> documentation for setup and operations.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">What does the license node limit control?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">The node limit on your Pro license defines how many <strong>Community edition</strong> nodes you can add under Node Management in 1Panel. Adding a community node consumes one slot from that quota; you choose which Pro license supplies the quota when you configure the node.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">Can I use multiple Pro licenses for different nodes?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">Yes. In <strong>License Management</strong> you can import and keep multiple Pro licenses. When you add a node as Pro edition, you assign an <strong>unbound</strong> Pro license to that node, so different nodes can each use their own license. Community nodes, by contrast, draw from your licenses’ community-node quota as described above.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-5">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-gray-800 font-semibold">Can I deactivate and reactivate a license?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">Yes. You can deactivate it in the current app and reactivate it on another device during the license validity period.</p>
        </details>

